  I had to push the arm all the way forward for enough of the cable to grab
  when tightening down on it.  Is this not the correct method for hooking up
  the cable?  I have not tested after the engine is warm since I have 
not had
  a chance to deal with the alternator cooling boot issue yet. I'm perusing
  the archives at this time but no luck so far.

